  "title": "Clinic Assistant",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking a dedicated and experienced Clinic Assistant to join our Obstetrics &amp; Gynaecology (O&amp;G) specialist clinic. The ideal candidate should have prior experience in an O&amp;G setup, possess strong patient-service skills, and be able to support clinic operations efficiently in a fast-paced environment. This role involves direct patient interaction, administrative duties, and clinical support to ensure smooth day-to-day operations and exceptional patient care.</p>\n<h2>Key Responsibilities</h2>\n<p><strong>1. Patient Registration &amp; Front Desk Duties</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Greet, register, and check-in patients warmly and professionally.</li>\n  <li>Verify patient particulars and insurance information.</li>\n  <li>Manage appointment scheduling, follow-ups, and cancellations.</li>\n  <li>Handle incoming calls, emails, and patient enquiries.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>2. Billing &amp; Financial Counselling</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Perform billing using clinic systems.</li>\n  <li>Process payments for consultations, scans, and procedures.</li>\n  <li>Explain cost estimates for O&amp;G services.</li>\n  <li>Handle Medisave, insurance, and corporate billing.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>3. Clinical Support</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prepare consultation rooms.</li>\n  <li>Assist doctors during consultations or minor procedures.</li>\n  <li>Prepare antenatal, consent, and admission forms.</li>\n  <li>Measure vital signs and assist with simple clinical tasks.</li>\n  <li>Handle urine tests, pregnancy tests, and specimen labelling.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>4. Obstetrics-Specific Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Assist in antenatal care and patient flow.</li>\n  <li>Provide information on scans, NIPT, antenatal labs, and delivery processes.</li>\n  <li>Ensure correct ordering and dispatch of samples.</li>\n  <li>Prepare required forms for patients at 32/35 weeks.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate CTG appointments and external referrals.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>5. Administrative &amp; Operational Duties</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Maintain inventory of medications, supplements, and consumables.</li>\n  <li>Receive and check stock deliveries.</li>\n  <li>Ensure cleanliness of clinic and equipment.</li>\n  <li>Prepare end-of-day reports and cash reconciliation.</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with SOPs and confidentiality requirements.</li>\n</ul>",
